WEBVTT

00:01.360 --> 00:04.090
Previously on
Pretty Little Liars...
Mona, we need your help.

00:04.130 --> 00:06.064
EMILY: We just found out that
Ali's at the police station.

00:06.100 --> 00:07.237
She's talking to the cops.

00:07.270 --> 00:08.589
But I'm already number one
on her hit list.

00:08.640 --> 00:10.767
If Alison finds out
I'm siding with you guys,

00:10.810 --> 00:13.108
I'm afraid to think of how far
she'd go to stop me.

00:13.140 --> 00:14.471
We never had our talk.

00:14.510 --> 00:15.499
I'm tired of talking.

00:17.110 --> 00:18.600
Happy graduation.

00:18.650 --> 00:19.674
Spence.

00:19.720 --> 00:20.709
SPENCER: I love you.

00:22.390 --> 00:23.379
BETHANY: Iwonder
if I can trust anyone

00:23.420 --> 00:24.387
in that family.

00:24.420 --> 00:25.580
Did Alison know Bethany?

00:25.620 --> 00:26.689
Where are you?

00:26.720 --> 00:28.119
Wait, I can't hear you.

00:28.160 --> 00:30.185
( horn honking )
( tires screeching )

00:30.230 --> 00:31.629
Spencer Hastings,
you're under arrest

00:31.660 --> 00:33.525
for the murder of
Bethany Young.

00:33.560 --> 00:35.118
I-I-I didn't do this.

00:35.160 --> 00:36.491
Where are we going?
To Mona's.

00:36.530 --> 00:38.225
She found proof.

00:38.270 --> 00:40.397
Oh, my God.
Mona!

00:40.440 --> 00:42.101
HOLBROOK: Although
we did not find a body,

00:42.140 --> 00:44.438
we have ruled
this a homicide.

00:45.840 --> 00:47.501
* Just hear those
sleigh bells jingling *

00:47.540 --> 00:50.270
* Ring-ting-tingling, too

00:50.310 --> 00:52.175
* Come on,
it's lovely weather *

00:52.220 --> 00:54.814
* For a sleigh ride
together with you *

00:54.850 --> 00:56.818
* Outside the snow is falling

00:56.850 --> 00:59.182
* And friends are calling,
"Yoo hoo" *

00:59.220 --> 01:00.756
So what did you
get for Toby?

01:00.790 --> 01:03.520
I'm abstaining from
Christmas this year, remember?

01:03.560 --> 01:04.857
When you're out on bail
for murder,

01:04.890 --> 01:07.154
it just feels like
the right thing to do.

01:07.200 --> 01:09.327
And he's okay with that?

01:09.370 --> 01:11.622
Well, he agreed
to not giving presents

01:11.670 --> 01:15.390
ifI agreed to surprising
each other with a gesture.

01:15.440 --> 01:16.702
Like the clowns?

01:16.740 --> 01:17.866
What clowns?

01:17.910 --> 01:20.470
Court jesters.
They're clowns, right?

01:23.680 --> 01:25.773
I've always
loved these windows.

01:28.250 --> 01:29.888
Let's make a wish.

01:29.920 --> 01:32.115
Yeah, let's make a wish
for Spencer.

01:32.160 --> 01:34.856
Guys, Santa is not bringing me
a stay-out-of-jail-free card.

01:39.460 --> 01:41.121
Han, want a snowflake?

01:42.670 --> 01:44.626
The last time I was here,
it was with Mona.

01:47.170 --> 01:49.400
What'd you wish for?

01:49.440 --> 01:51.203
You're my first
friend, Hanna.

01:51.240 --> 01:53.731
I wished for us
to always stay close.

01:53.780 --> 01:54.872
We will.

01:54.910 --> 01:56.605
Besties forever.

01:56.650 --> 01:58.106
I promise.

01:59.450 --> 02:01.475
So what'd you wish for?

02:01.520 --> 02:03.317
Jimmy Choos.

02:03.350 --> 02:04.612
Oh, you're getting those.

02:04.650 --> 02:06.356
Iam?

02:06.390 --> 02:08.551
If Santa doesn't bring 'em,
we'll steal 'em.

02:12.930 --> 02:15.353
Wishes don't come true,
Emily.

02:15.400 --> 02:17.265
If they did,
people wouldn't die.

02:18.600 --> 02:20.465
I'm still
holding out hope.

02:20.500 --> 02:22.900
Hope is a dirty
four-letter word.

02:22.940 --> 02:24.862
We live in an "A" world.

02:24.910 --> 02:26.901
They still haven't found
Mona's body.

02:26.940 --> 02:28.271
Yeah, that's because

02:28.310 --> 02:30.540
"A" likes to bury
the bodies herself.

02:30.580 --> 02:33.310
Yeah, and then
throw Ice Balls.

02:33.350 --> 02:34.942
I swear Alison is
throwing this party

02:34.980 --> 02:36.641
to rub it in our faces.

02:36.690 --> 02:39.181
I ruined your lives and now
I'm the belle of the ball.

02:39.220 --> 02:40.812
Technically,
she only ruined my life.

02:40.860 --> 02:43.420
Ruin one of us,
ruin all of us.

02:43.460 --> 02:45.826
Yeah, I'd rather dance
on dead monkeys

02:45.860 --> 02:47.498
than go to Ali's
stupid Ice Ball.

02:47.530 --> 02:49.828
Dead monkeys?

02:49.870 --> 02:52.737
Ali got everything
she wanted.

02:52.770 --> 02:55.330
Mona's gone,
Bethany's dead,

02:55.370 --> 02:57.509
and now she's making
Spencer go down for it.

02:58.840 --> 03:00.671
Is that a reporter
or a cop?

03:00.710 --> 03:01.870
Neither.

03:01.910 --> 03:02.945
That pen's too nice.

03:02.980 --> 03:04.845
My money's on a lawyer.

03:04.880 --> 03:06.677
Hanna Marin?

03:06.720 --> 03:08.176
Yes.

03:11.250 --> 03:12.285
Told you.

03:12.320 --> 03:14.413
Mona Vanderwaal retained me
to handle her affairs

03:14.460 --> 03:15.711
in the event
of her demise.

03:15.760 --> 03:18.354
I was instructed to wait
30 days after her death,

03:18.390 --> 03:19.857
then deliver this to you
personally.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.558
Merry Christmas.

03:23.600 --> 03:25.898
Bah humbug.

03:25.930 --> 03:27.466
I'm afraid to open it.

03:36.850 --> 03:39.648
These are drawings
of Ali's house.

03:39.680 --> 03:41.409
Yeah, and all of her
hiding places.

03:41.450 --> 03:44.010
It's from Mona.

03:44.050 --> 03:46.553
"Hey, Han.
If you're reading this..."

03:46.590 --> 03:48.410
MONA: She's still
playing the game

03:48.460 --> 03:50.678
and I'm talking to you
from the grave.

03:50.730 --> 03:53.494
But I went out fighting
and that's what you need to do.

03:53.530 --> 03:55.725
Promise me
you won't gIve up, Hanna.

03:55.760 --> 03:57.728
You have to keep looking.

03:57.770 --> 03:59.761
Kisses, M.

04:01.800 --> 04:04.405
I promised Mona
we'd always stick together.

04:05.970 --> 04:08.438
Well, you have to figure,
"A" keeps souvenirs, right?

04:08.480 --> 04:09.879
You mean Alison.

04:09.910 --> 04:12.310
Different name,
same bitch.

04:12.350 --> 04:14.375
There has to be something
in Ali's house that proves

04:14.420 --> 04:16.479
she killed Bethany.

04:16.520 --> 04:17.589
And Spencer didn't.

04:17.620 --> 04:18.985
I think Mona
just handed us a way

04:19.020 --> 04:20.510
to give you a Christmas,
Spence.

04:20.560 --> 04:22.778
And your
stay-out-of-jail-free card.

04:22.830 --> 04:25.390
( bell ringing )

04:28.000 --> 04:29.592
Hey, Santa.

04:36.610 --> 04:37.804
Thank you.

04:42.380 --> 04:43.779
Oh, my God.

04:43.810 --> 04:45.869
EMILY: Is that us?

04:48.420 --> 04:49.489
"'A' takes a holiday.

04:49.520 --> 04:51.010
You should, too."

05:05.500 --> 05:08.037
( banging )

05:08.070 --> 05:09.958
( panting )

05:17.110 --> 05:18.600
Mom.

05:18.650 --> 05:21.448
She's got a lot
to show you.

05:21.480 --> 05:22.981
Pay attention.

05:31.560 --> 05:33.551
* Got a secret,
can you keep it? *

05:33.600 --> 05:36.091
* Swear this one you'll save

05:36.130 --> 05:38.690
_* Better lock it
In your pocket *

05:38.730 --> 05:41.369
* Taking this one
to the grave *

05:41.400 --> 05:43.539
* IfI show you, then I know

05:43.570 --> 05:46.403
* You won't tell what I said

05:46.440 --> 05:48.738
* 'Cause two can keep
a secret *

05:48.780 --> 05:51.101
* If one of them is dead

06:24.780 --> 06:29.513
( piano music playing )

06:55.940 --> 06:57.601
I know you'd told me
never to leave the house

06:57.650 --> 06:59.811
without my face on,
but as a corpse,

06:59.850 --> 07:03.684
this is the best I can do
for your Ice Ball.

07:03.720 --> 07:05.449
This isn't real.

07:09.090 --> 07:10.887
You were quite
the little pianist.

07:12.900 --> 07:14.197
Is that me?

07:14.230 --> 07:15.697
You don't remember?

07:18.030 --> 07:20.191
It's not pretty.

07:20.240 --> 07:21.935
But you need to see it.

07:21.970 --> 07:24.029
See what?

07:24.070 --> 07:26.004
Wait for it.

07:29.110 --> 07:30.805
( hitting dead key)

08:05.750 --> 08:07.479
Alison!

08:08.680 --> 08:10.113
I didn't mean to,

08:10.150 --> 08:11.742
but I found your
hiding place.

08:11.790 --> 08:15.248
Did you and Daddy give me
the same present?

08:15.290 --> 08:17.588
I don't know
what you mean.

08:17.630 --> 08:20.258
Daddy will think
it's funny when I tell him.

08:20.300 --> 08:23.121
There are not two dresses.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.899
I think you need glasses.

08:27.640 --> 08:29.631
You only saw one dress.

08:29.670 --> 08:33.003
You found the present,
one present.

08:33.040 --> 08:37.204
You opened it
and there was one dress.

08:37.250 --> 08:40.071
Why, Mommy?

08:40.120 --> 08:41.610
Because I don't want
Daddy to leave us.

08:41.650 --> 08:44.187
And he will, if you tell him
about the dresses.

08:48.790 --> 08:50.781
I'll say whatever
you want me to.

08:50.830 --> 08:52.286
Good girl.

08:52.330 --> 08:53.797
Now tell me what happened.

08:53.830 --> 08:55.650
The real story.

08:55.700 --> 08:57.964
I was playing the piano.

08:58.000 --> 09:01.037
I looked inside of it
and found one present,

09:01.070 --> 09:02.958
one yellow dress.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.160
Good girl.

09:05.210 --> 09:07.030
One more time.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.604
I was playing the piano.

09:08.640 --> 09:10.642
I looked inside of it
and found one present,

09:10.680 --> 09:12.614
one yellow dress.

09:12.650 --> 09:15.175
And the monster was born.

09:15.220 --> 09:17.279
Who was
the other dress for?

09:19.150 --> 09:20.686
Was it Bethany?

09:23.090 --> 09:25.581
It's not going to be
that easy, bitch.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.249
( glass shatters )

09:36.640 --> 09:38.733
SPENCER: Ali made
hiding things into a game.

09:40.380 --> 09:42.940
TOBY: You're out on bail
for a murder charge, Spencer.

09:45.810 --> 09:47.812
SPENCER: Well,
it's not a perfect plan,

09:47.850 --> 09:48.919
but it's all I've got.

09:52.990 --> 09:54.958
And I saw the look
on my mom's face

09:54.990 --> 09:57.322
after we met my lawyers
for the last time.

09:59.190 --> 10:00.157
We've already lost.

10:00.200 --> 10:01.952
It's not over yet.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.321
But, hey, what if Ali
leaves the dance early?

10:04.370 --> 10:06.224
She won't.

10:06.270 --> 10:08.363
Aria and Emily
are gonna find a reason

10:08.400 --> 10:10.061
to keep her there.

10:10.110 --> 10:12.305
And you will be here to warn us
if anything goes wrong.

10:16.240 --> 10:19.368
I thought everybody was
splitting up on Christmas.

10:19.410 --> 10:21.378
No, we're all gonna
catch up with our parents

10:21.420 --> 10:23.411
before the snow starts.

10:23.450 --> 10:25.884
Mm, sounds like
you've got it all figured out.

10:27.290 --> 10:31.249
Toby, this might be
my last Christmas.

10:31.290 --> 10:32.928
Spencer...

10:37.000 --> 10:38.024
So...

10:51.250 --> 10:52.979
Merry-ho-ho.

10:53.020 --> 10:55.170
Nice gesture.

10:55.220 --> 10:56.812
Thanks.

10:59.350 --> 11:01.011
( indistinct chatter )

11:01.060 --> 11:02.857
* The lights are bright

11:02.890 --> 11:03.982
* It's cold tonight

11:04.030 --> 11:04.780
MAN 1: Merry Christmas.

11:06.160 --> 11:07.696
MAN 2: Merry
Christmas to you, too.

11:09.460 --> 11:11.189
Merry Christmas.

11:12.800 --> 11:14.791
Okay, where's my friend
Claire?

11:19.840 --> 11:21.398
I haven't signed
since fat camp.

11:21.440 --> 11:23.249
My bunkmate was
hard of hearing.

11:23.280 --> 11:24.679
Merry Christmas.

11:28.780 --> 11:31.112
What's wrong?

11:31.150 --> 11:33.186
I'm pretty sure that
some kid peed on me,

11:33.220 --> 11:34.187
and that mean little girl,

11:34.220 --> 11:35.448
she keeps calling me
dumb-dumb.

11:35.490 --> 11:37.026
What mean girl?

11:37.060 --> 11:38.379
Ali's little mini-me.

11:39.760 --> 11:41.455
Right there,
there she is.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.798
Call her anything
you want.

11:43.830 --> 11:45.195
She can't hear you.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.905
Get over here.

11:49.940 --> 11:51.407
All of you.

11:58.210 --> 11:59.507
I'm only gonna say this once.

11:59.550 --> 12:02.178
You mess with Claire,
you deal with me.

12:02.220 --> 12:03.949
I'm shaking with fear.

12:05.920 --> 12:07.956
You better start looking
over your shoulder,

12:07.990 --> 12:09.855
because you're making
a lot of enemies.

12:09.890 --> 12:12.723
And in Rosewood,
bitches get buried.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.991
This place blows.
Let's get out of here.

12:18.830 --> 12:22.231
Hey, you guys,
you don't need a leader.

12:22.270 --> 12:23.806
You just need each other.

12:23.840 --> 12:26.331
I said let's go!

12:33.180 --> 12:34.818
Losers.

12:39.050 --> 12:40.017
Well, I would say that

12:40.060 --> 12:42.085
you put the fear
of Hanna in her.

12:42.120 --> 12:44.884
Well, Mona used to say
when someone shows you

12:44.930 --> 12:46.420
who they are,
believe them.

12:47.530 --> 12:49.794
I don't think
people change, Caleb.

12:49.830 --> 12:52.025
They just get better
at hiding it.

12:53.200 --> 12:54.428
But mean girls
stay mean.

13:06.350 --> 13:10.138
* O come, let us adore him

13:10.190 --> 13:14.012
* O come,
let us adore him *

13:14.060 --> 13:18.383
* O come, let us adore him

13:18.430 --> 13:21.251
