I know you wanted to keep it
low-key this holiday,

13:31.140 --> 13:33.574
but this is for tonight.

13:33.610 --> 13:36.078
Is it an Ali-decoder ring?

13:36.110 --> 13:37.441
( chuckles )

13:41.120 --> 13:42.917
Ezra, they're beautiful.

13:42.950 --> 13:44.019
Thank you.

13:44.050 --> 13:46.189
And Mandi at the boutique

13:46.220 --> 13:49.314
said it might go well
with this.

13:51.090 --> 13:52.626
All right, if this is low-key,

13:52.660 --> 13:55.197
I'm afraid to ask
what full-on Christmas

13:55.230 --> 13:56.322
looks like
at the Fitzgerald house.

13:56.360 --> 13:57.861
Oh, yeah, don't ask.

13:57.900 --> 14:00.164
It's like how many ponies
can you get?

14:00.200 --> 14:01.599
Seriously?

14:01.640 --> 14:03.198
No.

14:03.240 --> 14:04.161
Ezra?

14:05.910 --> 14:08.299
Well, I got two ponies,
but I only asked for one.

14:10.050 --> 14:11.369
Merry Christmas.

14:13.250 --> 14:14.547
You got a minute?

14:14.580 --> 14:16.070
What do you want?

14:16.120 --> 14:19.248
So it looks like you and Paige
worked things out.

14:21.120 --> 14:23.156
Why doesn't Jenna
come over here and talk to me?

14:23.190 --> 14:25.158
And you don't have to be
her eyes and ears.

14:25.190 --> 14:27.124
She can still hear, right?

14:27.160 --> 14:28.491
Jenna's not a bad person.

14:28.530 --> 14:30.020
You just wouldn't
know that because

14:30.070 --> 14:31.628
Alison convinced you
that she was the enemy.

14:31.670 --> 14:33.297
Is that all?

14:33.340 --> 14:36.468
All right, I just wanted
to say Merry Christmas.

14:36.500 --> 14:39.105
Yeah.

14:39.140 --> 14:40.437
PAIGE: It's not
what I want.

14:40.480 --> 14:42.300
It's what you want.

14:44.480 --> 14:45.674
What's wrong?

14:45.710 --> 14:47.268
Nothing.

14:47.320 --> 14:50.448
My parents want me
to come to California
after Christmas.

14:50.490 --> 14:53.152
Well, that sounds
like a fun winter break.

14:54.290 --> 14:55.450
Look up.

15:04.270 --> 15:06.568
Well, let's see
how you look.

15:13.040 --> 15:14.302
Wow.

15:15.340 --> 15:17.308
It's a Christmas miracle.

15:38.400 --> 15:39.628
( sighs )

15:39.670 --> 15:42.298
I still don't see
All anywhere.

15:42.340 --> 15:44.308
She's probably waiting
to make her grand entrance.

15:44.340 --> 15:46.228
Timed to the perfect song.

15:46.270 --> 15:48.374
Well, we can't leave
until she gets here, so...

15:50.050 --> 15:52.041
I'm going to go have my picture
taken with Santa Claus.

16:04.490 --> 16:06.458
I think you know what
I want for Christmas.

16:06.490 --> 16:09.596
And I think you know
I'll do whatever I can
to help you get it.

16:12.530 --> 16:14.066
Hanna and I
are headed to her house

16:14.100 --> 16:15.465
the second All gets here.

16:15.500 --> 16:18.139
We'll make sure
she stays here, Spencer.

16:18.170 --> 16:20.206
You've been a very good girl
this year.

16:20.240 --> 16:22.071
Santa won't let you down.

16:22.110 --> 16:23.748
( laughter )

