* Holiday...

18:18.490 --> 18:19.855
ARIA: Who is that?

18:25.630 --> 18:26.767
Hey.

18:26.800 --> 18:27.869
Aren't you supposed
to be on "A" watch?

18:27.900 --> 18:29.458
Yeah.
You need to see this.

18:29.500 --> 18:30.501
What is it?

18:30.540 --> 18:32.758
I just saw Ali
kissing Santa Claus.

18:32.810 --> 18:34.175
Come on.

18:44.390 --> 18:45.345
( gasps )

18:45.390 --> 18:46.140
Jeez, Hanna!

18:46.190 --> 18:47.748
Do not sneak up on me
like that.

18:47.790 --> 18:48.711
I'm sorry.

18:50.760 --> 18:53.456
Okay, if we're
the only ones here,
why are we whispering?

18:53.500 --> 18:54.728
I don't know.

18:54.760 --> 18:56.227
Can we just talk
in a normal voice?

18:56.260 --> 18:58.399
Because this is
spooklng me out.

18:58.430 --> 18:59.761
Here, you take
the upstairs.

18:59.800 --> 19:00.767
I'll take the downstairs.

19:00.800 --> 19:03.598
Okay, on a creepy scale,

19:03.640 --> 19:05.665
how high would you rate
breaking into Ali's house?

19:05.710 --> 19:08.838
On a scale of 1 to 10,
it's a 20.

19:12.750 --> 19:14.172
They were just here.

19:15.480 --> 19:16.617
Was it a guy or a girl?
Guy.

19:16.650 --> 19:18.208
Are you sure?
Yes, I'm sure.

19:18.250 --> 19:20.389
I definitely got a sense of
"male butt."

19:20.420 --> 19:23.253
Okay, well, I'm gonna go
take my photo with Santa Claus.

19:24.690 --> 19:27.693
Come in closer
to Santa Claus.

19:27.730 --> 19:29.721
( guffaws )

19:31.730 --> 19:33.789
Merry Christmas!

19:33.840 --> 19:35.637
( guffaws )

19:45.950 --> 19:48.248
You're on my list, Aria.

19:50.290 --> 19:51.314
The naughty one.

19:52.350 --> 19:53.556
Surprised to see you here.

19:53.590 --> 19:56.559
Yeah, not as surprised
as I am to see you.

19:56.590 --> 19:58.581
It's a charity ball.

19:58.630 --> 20:01.326
Giving back
to my community.

20:01.360 --> 20:03.828
I didn't realize that _
Rosewood was your community.

20:03.870 --> 20:06.430
The town has a lot
to offer.

20:06.470 --> 20:08.438
It's starting
to grow on me.

20:08.470 --> 20:10.529
That's spoken like a guy

20:10.570 --> 20:12.765
who maybe met a girl
that he likes.

20:12.810 --> 20:14.835
What brings you out
tonight, Aria?

20:14.880 --> 20:16.768
Same as you.

20:16.810 --> 20:18.698
It feels good
to give back.

20:18.750 --> 20:19.978
I don't know why

20:20.010 --> 20:22.274
I have such a hard time
believing you.

20:24.390 --> 20:26.585
My boyfriend's
probably looking for me.

20:26.620 --> 20:28.315
That's a pretty dress.

20:28.360 --> 20:30.851
Tell Ezra I think
he has good taste.

20:34.760 --> 20:36.796
Aria and Emily
lost Alison.

20:36.830 --> 20:39.526
Oh, well, I think
I just found her.

21:35.960 --> 21:37.587
Merry Christmas, Ali.

21:43.970 --> 21:46.495
( music playing )

22:09.420 --> 22:10.580
You don't need
to be afraid.

22:12.590 --> 22:13.591
( Emily gasps )

22:13.630 --> 22:14.949
I led you here,

22:15.000 --> 22:17.366
because I don't want Alison
to see us talking.

22:22.640 --> 22:24.835
You really get around,
Sydney.

22:24.870 --> 22:26.599
Does Jenna know
you're with Ali now?

22:29.080 --> 22:30.604
( gasps )

22:33.680 --> 22:36.945
When I first moved
to Rosewood,

22:36.980 --> 22:39.084
Alison offered to be
my friend.

22:41.660 --> 22:43.981
I made the mistake
of saying no.

22:45.130 --> 22:47.394
When she asked me
this time

22:47.430 --> 22:50.797
I gave her
the right answer.

22:50.830 --> 22:53.731
I promise you,
we're not the enemy.

22:53.770 --> 22:55.931
No, you're just
sleeping with the enemy.

22:55.970 --> 22:57.665
I'm not gay, Emily.

22:57.710 --> 22:59.109
That's not what I meant.

22:59.140 --> 23:01.131
Look, until someone puts
Ali away,

23:01.180 --> 23:04.672
we're doing
what we have to do to survive.

23:04.710 --> 23:07.611
I'm sure you and your friends
understand that.

23:12.650 --> 23:14.754
We think
she killed Mona.

23:14.790 --> 23:17.429
We do, too.

23:28.600 --> 23:29.760
Alison?

23:29.800 --> 23:31.006
There's this shop
in Le Marais

23:31.040 --> 23:33.429
that helps you make your
own fragrance.

23:33.480 --> 23:34.469
It's a tiny store,

23:34.510 --> 23:35.909
but I spent the
entire day there.

23:35.940 --> 23:37.168
The owner gets
you talking.

23:37.210 --> 23:38.370
And the next thing you know,
he's created a scent

23:38.410 --> 23:40.913
that's perfect for the person
you're telling him about.

23:42.820 --> 23:44.583
Thank you.

23:44.620 --> 23:48.511
Not just for the perfume,
but for coming to see me.

23:48.560 --> 23:50.755
When you lose someone,

23:50.790 --> 23:53.179
the first Christmas
is always the hardest.

23:55.230 --> 23:57.767
I think my mom is
still looking out for me.

23:57.800 --> 23:59.927
I'm sure she is.

23:59.970 --> 24:02.530
I had a dream about her
the other night.

24:02.570 --> 24:04.561
She came to warn me
about Mona.

24:05.810 --> 24:07.038
Mona can't hurt you
anymore.

24:07.070 --> 24:08.469
You know that.

24:10.280 --> 24:12.544
You can't
let your guard down, Ali.

24:12.580 --> 24:14.218
Your ex-frie_nds
are here tonight.

24:14.250 --> 24:16.718
And I don't think they came
to say Merry Christmas.

25:05.900 --> 25:08.095
What did you find, Hanna?

25:16.780 --> 25:18.145
REPORTER: ( on TV)
If the winds pick up,

25:18.180 --> 25:20.102
we could be looking
at blizzard conditions

25:20.150 --> 25:23.608
for the Rosewood area
on this blustery Christmas Eve.

25:23.650 --> 25:25.845
But don't worry, kids,
Santa has Rudolph

25:25.890 --> 25:27.915
to navigate his sleigh.

25:31.760 --> 25:34.024
Does the name Holly Varjak
mean anything to you?

25:35.900 --> 25:37.993
Spence?
What, Hanna?

25:38.030 --> 25:40.066
If All needs to get out of town
in a hurry,

25:40.100 --> 25:43.137
she's ready to go
as Holly Varjak.

25:47.710 --> 25:49.837
She's writing her
happy ending.

25:49.880 --> 25:51.245
To what?

25:51.280 --> 25:52.269
Breakfast at Tiffany's.

25:52.310 --> 25:54.972
Probably the movie,
not the book.

25:55.020 --> 25:57.045
Ezra always says that
she was his "Holly Golightly."

25:57.080 --> 25:58.945
And Paul Varjak was the guy
who convinced Holly

25:58.990 --> 26:00.241
that it was okay
to be loved.

26:00.290 --> 26:02.986
So in Ali's manic mind,
they got married.

26:03.020 --> 26:05.181
How do you fit
all of that information

26:05.230 --> 26:06.857
into your one head?

26:10.360 --> 26:11.463
What are those?

26:11.500 --> 26:15.334
Ali was talking to somebody
through the personal ads.

26:15.370 --> 26:18.567
Like she did with Mona
back when Mona was "A."

26:22.840 --> 26:26.071
If All was kissing Holbrook,
that would explain a lot.

26:26.110 --> 26:27.941
Yeah, like why Spencer's
about to go on trial for murder

26:27.980 --> 26:30.312
while Ali's weaving her way
through a winter wonderland.

26:30.350 --> 26:32.944
Ezra, what is it?

26:32.990 --> 26:34.981
Well, if Holbrook
is helping Ali,

26:35.020 --> 26:36.612
I want to know
when it started.

26:38.360 --> 26:39.918
Oh, my God.

26:39.960 --> 26:42.292
I promised All
I wouldn't tell

26:42.330 --> 26:45.026
because I thought
I was protecting everyone.

26:45.070 --> 26:47.163
But CeCe showed up
in New York that night.

26:47.200 --> 26:49.236
And All helped
to get her out of the country.

26:49.270 --> 26:50.965
You think Holbrook
was In on It?

26:51.010 --> 26:53.228
I think he helped
CeCe escape.

26:53.270 --> 26:55.101
And he did it for Ali.

26:55.140 --> 26:57.608
Looks like All
made a friend.

26:59.880 --> 27:01.768
PAIGE: She went
in there alone.

27:01.820 --> 27:03.139
They're heading
towards the exit.

27:03.180 --> 27:04.943
So is Holbrook.

27:04.990 --> 27:06.844
You guys follow Ali.

27:06.890 --> 27:07.857
We've got Santa.

27:07.890 --> 27:08.879
I'll grab Lucas.

27:11.830 --> 27:13.718
Detective Holbrook.

27:13.760 --> 27:15.990
May I have a word with you
for a second?

27:16.030 --> 27:17.224
Sure.

27:17.260 --> 27:19.797
( indistinct chattering )

27:49.860 --> 27:51.691
You're leaving your
own party, Ali?

27:51.730 --> 27:52.958
What's the rush?

28:00.440 --> 28:02.078
Alison?

28:12.090 --> 28:13.079
( door closing )

29:05.140 --> 29:06.232
ALISON: ( on tape )
Get out of my stuff

29:06.270 --> 29:07.237
or I'll kill you!

29:07.270 --> 29:08.874
( gasps )

29:15.880 --> 29:17.017
Where are you, Hanna?

29:17.050 --> 29:19.189
( cell phone ringing )

29:21.020 --> 29:22.351
What's wrong?

29:22.390 --> 29:23.618
CALEB: We think
Ali left the party.

29:23.660 --> 29:25.924
I tried calling Hanna
but she's not picking up.

29:27.860 --> 29:28.849
Damn it.

29:28.900 --> 29:30.492
CALEB: We're our way.

29:37.140 --> 29:38.835
Hanna, you've got to
get out of there.

30:23.320 --> 30:24.844
Where did you go?

30:29.260 --> 30:31.888
( music playing )

30:37.000 --> 30:38.865
( gasps )

30:43.970 --> 30:44.959
Mad Hatter?

30:48.010 --> 30:49.375
Mad Hatter.

31:23.280 --> 31:25.145
( cell phone buzzes )

31:58.050 --> 31:59.176
Hanna!

31:59.210 --> 32:02.509
God, I only had
one pen pal.

32:02.550 --> 32:04.188
All had a fan club.

32:07.750 --> 32:09.581
"Can't wait to see you."

32:09.620 --> 32:10.587
Oh, my God.

32:10.620 --> 32:13.157
Ali knew Bethany.

32:13.190 --> 32:15.158
And she invited her here
for Labor Day.

32:51.500 --> 32:53.229
TOBY: Damn it,
where are you?

32:54.770 --> 32:56.237
( door creaks )

33:01.510 --> 33:03.239
Spence?

33:06.380 --> 33:07.369
Spencer?

33:27.130 --> 33:28.097
Hanna?

33:29.400 --> 33:31.106
Spencer?

33:31.140 --> 33:32.402
Come on.

33:52.560 --> 33:55.199
( screaming )

33:56.600 --> 33:58.568
Come on, Hanna.
Come on.

34:05.440 --> 34:06.634
Hanna!

34:09.580 --> 34:10.535
Hanna?

34:10.580 --> 34:11.808
Hey. Hey.

34:11.850 --> 34:12.805
Come on.

34:12.850 --> 34:13.646
Hanna?

34:13.680 --> 34:16.069
Hey, please, please,
please, wake up.

34:16.120 --> 34:17.519
It's okay.

34:17.550 --> 34:18.517
( panting )

34:18.550 --> 34:19.517
Oh.

34:19.550 --> 34:20.619
Oh, my God.

34:20.650 --> 34:21.685
Are you okay?

34:21.720 --> 34:22.687
Hanna?

34:24.130 --> 34:25.188
It's okay, she's gone.

34:25.230 --> 34:26.549
She's gone.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.120
It's okay, she's gone.

34:32.230 --> 34:33.219
You're okay.

34:33.270 --> 34:35.192
Hey, you're okay.

34:44.410 --> 34:46.549
Give Mom and Grandma Bea
a big kiss for me.

34:46.580 --> 34:48.844
And I promise
I'll be on the road
as soon as It's clear.

34:49.880 --> 34:51.689
Thanks, Dad.

34:51.720 --> 34:52.709
I love you, too.

34:52.750 --> 34:54.217
This is amazing.

34:54.260 --> 34:56.751
Hanna, this letter proves
that Alison knew Bethany

34:56.790 --> 34:58.826
and lured her here
on Labor Day.

34:58.860 --> 35:00.555
This could create
enough reasonable doubt

35:00.590 --> 35:01.625
to clear Spencer.

35:04.700 --> 35:06.588
I don't want to say
the "H" word,

35:06.630 --> 35:11.636
but I am feeling cautiously
optimistic tonight.

35:11.670 --> 35:13.228
( clock chimes )

35:13.270 --> 35:14.828
( sighs )

35:14.880 --> 35:17.337
Merry Christmas.

35:17.380 --> 35:18.642
Merry Christmas.

35:18.680 --> 35:21.649
And her heart grew
three sizes that day.

35:22.780 --> 35:23.747
Merry Christmas.

35:23.780 --> 35:24.747
Merry Christmas.

35:24.790 --> 35:26.280
Merry Christmas.

35:26.320 --> 35:27.116
Merry Christmas.

35:27.150 --> 35:34.192
* Glory to the newborn king

35:34.230 --> 35:37.757
* Hark the herald angels sing

35:37.800 --> 35:41.429
* Glory to the newborn king

35:42.540 --> 35:44.167
How was the party?

35:48.480 --> 35:51.244
Ignoring me
won't make me go away.

35:51.280 --> 35:52.702
It'll just make me mad.

36:02.690 --> 36:03.714
Boo!
( gasps )

36:03.760 --> 36:05.580
( laughing )

36:08.930 --> 36:11.899
I'm scared, okay?

36:11.930 --> 36:13.727
Is that what you wanted
to hear?

36:13.770 --> 36:15.397
( sighs )

36:15.440 --> 36:16.532
It wasn't as gratifying

36:16.570 --> 36:18.162
as I thought
it was gonna be.

36:19.810 --> 36:21.903
What do you want me
to do?

36:21.940 --> 36:24.545
What do you want me to say
to make you go away?

36:27.250 --> 36:28.547
Wait for it.

36:31.790 --> 36:34.350
Tell me if Tiny Tim
will live.

36:34.390 --> 36:36.381
Do we have to watch this?

36:36.420 --> 36:37.819
It's depressing.

36:37.860 --> 36:40.351
If you think
you're depressed now,

36:40.390 --> 36:42.221
look over there.

37:15.300 --> 37:16.995
VVhen?

37:17.030 --> 37:18.588
Does it matter?

37:19.630 --> 37:21.666
It does to me.

37:21.700 --> 37:23.588
And only you.

37:24.910 --> 37:27.470
You look pretty good,
considering

37:27.510 --> 37:30.229
that they never found
your legs.

37:35.950 --> 37:38.282
Do I know you?

37:45.830 --> 37:47.479
Mom.

37:47.530 --> 37:49.851
It's all my fault.

37:49.900 --> 37:51.390
Look at me.

37:52.670 --> 37:54.023
I'm not dead.

37:54.070 --> 37:56.766
They'll be coming
for you soon.

37:58.370 --> 38:00.406
I'm sorry.

38:12.850 --> 38:15.887
( creepy whispers and moans )

38:15.920 --> 38:17.854
Am I going to hell?

38:21.030 --> 38:23.658
No. No.

38:23.700 --> 38:24.928
No!

38:24.970 --> 38:26.062
No!

38:26.100 --> 38:27.089
Please!

38:27.130 --> 38:29.337
Let me out!

38:29.370 --> 38:31.463
Mona!

38:31.510 --> 38:32.909
Mona!

38:32.940 --> 38:34.373
Wake up, bitch!

38:34.410 --> 38:36.799
It's Christmas.

38:36.840 --> 38:39.809
And I promise
you don't want to miss it.

38:46.390 --> 38:48.915
My mom called her friend
at Highway Patrol.

38:48.960 --> 38:52.418
They don't expect the roads
to be cleared until tomorrow.

38:52.460 --> 38:54.690
I'm so sorry, Em.

38:54.730 --> 38:56.550
This is the first time
I won't be with my parents

38:56.600 --> 38:58.591
on Christmas.

38:58.630 --> 39:00.393
Yeah, me too.

39:00.430 --> 39:03.467
You know, my mom always said
Christmas was wherever we were

39:03.500 --> 39:06.401
as long as
we were together.

39:06.440 --> 39:07.600
And we are...

39:07.640 --> 39:09.471
together.

39:10.540 --> 39:12.599
Seriously?

39:12.650 --> 39:14.709
Now that is a gesture.

39:14.750 --> 39:15.978
Wow.

39:16.020 --> 39:18.614
TOGETHER:
Merry Christmas.

39:18.650 --> 39:20.538
Oh, my God.

39:20.590 --> 39:28.122
* Have yourself
a merry little Christmas *

39:28.160 --> 39:33.564
* Let your heart be light

39:33.600 --> 39:36.569
* From now on

39:36.600 --> 39:42.379
* Our troubles will be
out of SIght *

39:46.710 --> 39:48.769
Hey, you okay?

39:48.820 --> 39:49.946
My parents don't think
Rosewood's

39:49.980 --> 39:52.483
a safe place anymore.

39:52.520 --> 39:53.919
They don't want me
to visit California,

39:53.950 --> 39:55.611
they want me
to move there.

39:55.660 --> 39:59.118
Wait, before graduation?

39:59.160 --> 40:01.822
I'll have enough credits
by the end of spring quarter.

40:05.670 --> 40:07.126
I just thought
we had more time.

40:09.570 --> 40:14.678
*_ Here we are
as In olden days *

40:14.710 --> 40:20.398
* Happy golden days of yore

40:21.820 --> 40:23.014
* Faithful friends
who are dear to us *

40:23.050 --> 40:25.780
Mona should be
here tonight.

40:25.820 --> 40:28.618
The only reason
we're celebrating
is because of her.

40:38.500 --> 40:39.524
Christmas chicken.

40:39.570 --> 40:41.094
ALL: Yeah!

40:44.670 --> 40:47.059
Okay, let's all
say a prayer.

40:47.110 --> 40:49.874
* Until then

40:49.910 --> 40:52.947
* We'll just have
to muddle through *

40:52.980 --> 40:55.141
* Somehow

41:00.750 --> 41:05.949
*_ Here we are
as In olden days *

41:05.990 --> 41:12.725
* Happy golden days of yore

41:12.770 --> 41:18.936
* Faithful friends
who are dear to us *

41:18.970 --> 41:25.705
* Gather near to us
once more *

41:25.750 --> 41:28.969
( tapping on glass )

41:29.020 --> 41:30.248
To this family.

41:30.280 --> 41:32.919
May we always
stay together.

41:32.950 --> 41:34.656
Cheers.

41:34.690 --> 41:35.952
ALL: Cheers.

41:40.030 --> 41:43.249
( bells jingling )

41:45.770 --> 41:46.725
Santa?

41:51.840 --> 41:55.037
* And have yourself

41:55.080 --> 41:57.776
* A merry
little Christmas now *

41:57.810 --> 41:58.947
Oh, my God.

41:58.980 --> 42:00.140
Who did this?

42:00.180 --> 42:01.818
Em?
Not me.

42:15.760 --> 42:17.921
Merry Christmas,
bitches.
